All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Call
The Call class represents the "CALL" move in the poker game.
Card
The Card class represents a playing card, which consists of a rank and a suit.
Card.Rank
Enum representing the rank of a card (Two, Three, ..., Ace).
Card.Suit
Enum representing the suit of a card (Spades, Clubs, Diamonds, Hearts).
Croupier
The Croupier class provides utility methods for managing card distribution during a poker game.
Deck
The Deck class provides utility methods for creating and managing a deck of cards.
Exchange
The Exchange class represents the "EXCHANGE" move in the poker game.
Exit
The Exit class represents the "EXIT" move in the poker game.
Fold
The Fold class represents the "FOLD" move in the poker game.
Game
The Game class represents a poker game instance.
HandEvaluator
Class which is used to determine values of players hands and as a result, who has the strongest cards and won the game
Join
The Join class represents the "JOIN" move in the poker game.
Move
The Move interface defines the contract for all poker game moves.
NewGame
The NewGame class represents the "NEW_GAME" move in the poker game.
Player
The Player class represents a player in the poker game.
Raise
The Raise class represents the "RAISE" move in the poker game.
Status
The Status class represents the "STATUS" move in the poker game.
